    :OptimalPH "7.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :OptimalTemperature "37.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :PHMax "7.4"^^xsd:float ;
    :PHMin "6.6"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMax "45.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMin "20.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :hasOxygenNiche :Anaerobic ;
    :performsProcess :HydrogenotrophicMethanogenesis,
        :UptakeOfHydrogenInADM,
        :XhmEndogenousDecay ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "Methanospirillum hungatei is a hydrogenotrophic methanogen frequently found in syntrophic association with fatty-acid oxidisers in anaerobic digesters, reducing carbon dioxide to methane. In this ontology it is represented as a HydrogenotrophicMethanogen with literature-sourced environmental growth conditions. Sources: Ferry JG, Smith PH, Wolfe RS (1974) Methanospirillum hungatii gen. nov. sp. nov. Int J Syst Bacteriol 24:465-469." .

:Methanothrix_soehngenii a :AcetoclasticMethanogen,
        owl:NamedIndividual ;
    rdfs:label "Methanothrix soehngenii" ;
    :OptimalPH "7.6"^^xsd:float ;
    :OptimalTemperature "37.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :PHMax "8.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :PHMin "6.5"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMax "40.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMin "30.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :hasOxygenNiche :Anaerobic ;
    :performsProcess :AcetoclasticMethanogenesis,
        :UptakeOfAcetateInADM,
        :XacEndogenousDecay ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "Methanothrix soehngenii is an obligately acetoclastic methanogen (formerly Methanosaeta) that cleaves acetate to methane and carbon dioxide, dominant at low acetate concentrations in anaerobic digesters. In this ontology it is represented as a AcetoclasticMethanogen with literature-sourced environmental growth conditions. Sources: Huser BA, Wuhrmann K, Zehnder AJB (1982) Methanothrix soehngenii gen. nov. sp. nov., an acetotrophic methanogen. Arch Microbiol 132:1-9." .

:MgKP_Dissolution a :PhosphorusRemovalProcess,
