    :PHMax "8.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :PHMin "7.6"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMax "44.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMin "33.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :hasOxygenNiche :Aerobic ;
    :performsProcess :AerobicGrowthOfXaut,
        :AutotrophicNitrification,
        :LysisOfXaut ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "Nitrospira moscoviensis is a chemolithoautotrophic nitrite-oxidizing bacterium of the genus Nitrospira, a key K-strategist NOB in wastewater nitrification. In this ontology it is represented as a NitriteOxidizingBacteria with literature-sourced environmental growth conditions. Sources: Ehrich S, Behrens D, Lebedeva E, Ludwig W, Bock E (1995) A new obligately chemolithoautotrophic, nitrite-oxidizing bacterium, Nitrospira moscoviensis sp. nov. Arch Microbiol 164:16-23. [web-verified]" .

