    :PHMin "6.5"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMax "40.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :TemperatureMin "25.0"^^xsd:float ;
    :hasOxygenNiche :Anaerobic ;
    :performsProcess :AcidogenesisHighPH,
        :AcidogenesisLowPH,
        :DeathAndDecayOfSugarDegraders,
        :FermentationOfFSO,
        :UptakeOfSugarsInADM ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "Syntrophomonas wolfei is an anaerobic syntrophic fatty-acid-oxidising bacterium that ferments butyrate and other fatty acids to acetate and hydrogen in obligate syntrophy with methanogens. In this ontology it is represented as a AcidogenicBacteria with literature-sourced environmental growth conditions. Sources: McInerney MJ, Bryant MP, Hespell RB, Costerton JW (1981) Syntrophomonas wolfei gen. nov. sp. nov. Appl Environ Microbiol 41:1029-1039." .

