    rdfs:isDefinedBy "Tetrasphaera elongata is a polyphosphate-accumulating actinobacterium contributing to enhanced biological phosphorus removal, capable of fermentative metabolism and phosphate cycling. In this ontology it is represented as a PhosphateAccumulatingOrganisms with literature-sourced environmental growth conditions. Sources: Hanada S et al. (2002) Tetrasphaera elongata sp. nov., a polyphosphate-accumulating bacterium. Int J Syst Evol Microbiol 52:883-887." .

:Thauera_aromatica a :DenitrifyingBacteria,
